## 6. Summary Reference Table

| Concept | What it is | Where it lives | Example |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Storage Account** | Top-level namespace unit | Azure DNS + regional cluster | `mycompanystorage` |
| **DNS Endpoint** | Globally unique URL for the account | Azure global DNS | `mycompanystorage.blob.core.windows.net` |
| **Container** | Logical partition for blobs | Partition layer (metadata) | `user-uploads` |
| **Blob** | Individual object (any file type) | Extent store (storage nodes) | `avatar.jpg` |
| **Metadata record** | Per-blob index with content-type, size, tier, extent pointers | Partition layer | `{name, size, type, extents...}` |
| **Extent** | Physical chunk of blob bytes | Storage node disks | `Extent-A01` (up to 1 GB) |
| **Storage Node** | Physical server holding extents | Datacenter hardware | Node 1, 2, 3 |
| **LRS** | 3 copies in one datacenter | Single zone | Dev/test workloads |
| **ZRS** | 3 copies across 3 zones (synchronous) | 3 availability zones | Production workloads |
| **GRS** | ZRS/LRS + async geo-copy | 2 regions | Disaster recovery |
| **Access Tier** | Hot / Cool / Archive per blob | Metadata + physical media tier | `report.pdf → Cool` |
| **Virtual Directory** | Simulated folder via `/` prefix | Blob name prefix only | `images/avatar.jpg` |

